vectorData.altText: That's right!  The tunica albuginea surrounds the testicle. It consists of dense connective tissue and its high proportion of collagen fibres make it stain bright pink with eosin.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

This histological image depicts:

Tunica Albuginea (TA):
Dense fibrous CT capsule

Seminiferous Tubules (ST):
Location of sperm production (will be discussed in more detail). Supported by CT containing Interstitial (Leydig) cells which produce testosterone
